title: Tyrone Unsworth: Queensland police wrap up investigation into 13yo's assault - RN - ABC News (Australian Broadcasting Corporation)
text:
According to his aunt, Rebecca Unsworth, an argument over a girl triggered the incident. 
"Someone spat on a girl so Tyrone defended the girl," she said. 
"The other fellow who was in the argument went and found a fence paling and while Tyrone had his back turned hit him with it." 
After being discharged from hospital, Tyrone never went back to school. 
Instead, he moved to his grandfather's property in Upper Kedron, north west Brisbane, to recuperate. 
The teenager was found dead at that property four weeks later. 
"He was very different when he got out of hospital," Rebecca Unsworth said. 
"He might have been a bit worried and scared because of what had just happened." 
Education Queensland said Aspley State High School tried to contact Tyrone's family regularly following the assault but the principal, Jacquita Miller, declined to comment. 
Tyrone endured years of homophobic bullying , which took a toll on his mental health. 
While his family remains split on whether the 13-year-old was gay, his interest in women's clothing, makeup, and female pop singers made him an easy target in the playground.
